<br>
I just get so tired of this anti business attitude in our country (and probably other countries too) these days.  People don't stop to think about the economics of scale.  I have worked in retail for many years, including at Wal Mart a little over 10 years ago.  There is almost NO profit in retail because of the competition.  That leads to low wages.  But it also means that the jobs are incredibly easy to get and keep as long as you don't steal stuff or do drugs.<br>
<br>
Face it, not everyone has an advanced degree in rocket science or bio-chemistry, or is a corporate lawyer or one of the Hilton sisters.  Someone will always have to be the one ringing the rest of us up at Wal Mart.  Maybe if that person works hard enough they can become full time, or a manager there.  If they don't, they can go do something else.  Drive a truck, join the Army, dig ditches, whatever.  Thats what makes this country great.<br>
<br>
Until then, if you hate Wal mart stay away from them, just means one less person in line when I go to ring up. <p>Gnome &gt; all<br>
